# 🔧 KYC File Uploads & Aadhaar OTP Verification Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the implementation of actual file uploading (PDF, JPG, PNG formats) for government ID documents and workshop photos, replacing the legacy text URL input fields. It also introduces an Aadhaar OTP verification step to validate the applicant's Aadhaar number with their registered mobile number.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **File Format Constraints**: Standardized file uploads will restrict files to `.jpg, .jpeg, .png, and .pdf` formats with a maximum file size of 10MB.
> - **Aadhaar Verification Gating**: When a technician selects "Aadhaar Card" as their ID type, they **must** request and verify a mock 6-digit Aadhaar OTP before they are allowed to continue to the next registration step.
> - **Proxy Rules Update**: We will proxy the `/uploads` folder on the local dev servers so that `/uploads/filename.png` resolves natively from the backend (port 3000) for both customer (`4200`) and admin (`4201`) frontends without needing hardcoded hosts.

